  "reasoning": "Samsung 860 EVO SSD is not present in the ata_device_blacklist array (around lines 4562-4565). Similar devices like Samsung SSD 840 and 850 already have the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag set to disable queued TRIM support. The missing Samsung 860 EVO entry allows the device to use queued TRIM (ATA_CMD_FPDMA_SEND) which causes timeouts with the ASMedia ASM1062 controller. The fix requires adding Samsung 860 EVO to the blacklist with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags. The bug manifests at libata-scsi.c line 3510 where ata_fpdma_dsm_supported() returns true for Samsung 860 EVO, allowing queued TRIM to be used. The flag should have been disabled in libata-core.c at lines 2218-2221 where ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM is checked to disable queued TRIM support."
}

